reviews.review_text: This restaurant offers delicate and delicious dim sum and seafoods, which are traditional and affordable. The location is easy to be accessible and will be definitely re-visited in the coming days. Highly recommend!

Having tried the dinner menu, we were deeply impressed by the method in which the lobster and crab was made. The vegetable tasted fresh as well. Five dishes was more than enough for six people, and we were also given desserts for free. So satisfied with the stuffs service and the restaurants environment!

Not sure if same owner, place was newly renovated, much more cozy to dine this time, food still the same, they modified their menu for dimsum, the staff are great and friendly, still good price compared to other dimsum places.
Good place to have Chinese food with family, new menu, service and good environment.
New resturant, nice and clean. Price is fair.

The haw gow (steamed Dumplings shrimp) are the biggest I have seen . Food came fast, very tasty, sticky rice (leave wrapped) is a must, the books in between each table is nice added feature I have not seen before

Came here for dinner with my family. It was super delicious. The kids liked it very much. The portion is very generous and the price is very affordable. I will come again next time Kid-friendliness: Soy Sauce Chicken, Pineapple Sweet and Sour Shrimp, Fish Fillet, and Beef
$8.25 for small prawn dumplings seems too pricey! Chicken feet was really really good. One of the best I have had. Service was good too. Plus, there are books to read Food
Pretty good food with generous portion but unfortunately HK style restaurant with HK style bad services as well.

We went during their afternoon tea special. Ordered the curry beef brisket rice and satay beef noodle soup. Drinks came free. They ran out of egg tarts but offered to give taro puffs as a substitute. The food on par with most Hong Kong style cafe. The noodle soup was a bit bland but I didn t mind it.
Decent food with the worst services. Early dimsum has 10%off.

This long time Asian Cantonese style restaurant on Victoria st and 51 ave just received a full renovation. its brighter and mostly in booth sitting now. The menu is updated with a few more specialty dishes added. It opens for dimsum and full dinner and is very popular with the locals so be prepared to wait during the weekend. Reservation is accepted. Parking is pretty much off the surrounding streets. Food is decent and services are energetic and efficient. Prices are reasonable and plate volume is decent so good value for family meals. Recommended if you are in the area with the  bakeries, groceries and medical centers around. Great for lunch and dinner.
Can use credit card above $50.  Dimsum 10% off, available all day
Good food and good price!
Good price and the food meets the average Chinese food standard comparing to restaurants in Asia. Kid-friendliness: There are many kids books available.

Like the layout with small 2-person banquettes, larger 4-people banquettes, as well as family-size big tables. It was packed and vibing  at noon. Tried the dim sum, which was hit and miss. Hit: Beef rice noodle roll (soft, tender), fried bean curd roll with shrimp filling (crispy). Miss: steamed pork dumplings (large chewy pork pieces), steamed crispy bean curd with fish paste (too much liquid made it soggy), pan fried radish cake (too little radish).
DimSum has a narrow limited variety, will give 10% discount for dim sum. Food is okay but provide good service, busy with majority of seniors customers. Food
Reservation  recommended on Sundays. Kitchen could definitely use some help as we waited almost an hour  for our orders to arrive. Tea is charged $1.50/person, for a sub-par restaurant!!
For afternoon tea time, there are not many choices on Manu.

Visited Super Star as an alternate since Western Lake was full on a weekday at 10:30am.  The service was terrible.  Middle aged chinese ladies shouting, pointing, no smiles and not acknowledging after we made any requests (for sauce, more tea, etc.).  We watched them do the same thing to everyone whether you spoke mandarin, cantonese or english .. it didnt matter. The dim sum was mediocre at best for the price.  The restaurant is new, modern and still clean for now.  With so many choices especially in the same area we wont be returning.
The food is not yummy
No all day dim sum

My review with comes good intentions because I understand the struggles that small businesses face and I come with feedback and how to move forward with my experience. Clientele and food: Geriatric consumers. Which is why as a younger person, I need to advocate for the elderly. Our table was the youngest one, the rest are elderly people. Understand that geriatric patients often lose their sense of smell and taste and come with other health problems, HBP, diabetes, etc. As a community, we should be supporting everyone: local business and our community members. Two items are bad items: sui mai (meat stinks and is old, when you bring it near  to consumer it already had foul smell, the chiu chow dumpling was terribly made on a physical level but this is also the 2nd item that is foul (it was at a distance from me and I can already smell it from the table). Menu: needs to be updated to reflect their items. One error to note is squid tentacles in English but when served, its not tentacles and turns out the Chinese name is just squid. Fried quid tentacles is a rarity so if I see tentacles in English, I will order it. But it is not. You need to update the menu because that is flat out deceiving. Staff: The good, they have full staff. The bad, inefficient. I assume there is 1-2 front staff that is either the owner or affiliated with the small business because they CARE. They either huddle around and follow each other walking up and down (with the second person behind not doing anything and not looking around). There are quite a few staff that have dyed red hair. The long red hair literally yelled at me to give me the receipt so she can cross it off (this is when she served me squid tentacles and it was not tentacles, at that point, I asked my family if I red it wrong because clearly I remember seeing the word tentacles and thought perhaps they are giving us the wrong order. The other 2 red hair ladies have short hair, one with a similar haircut from TVB Moonlight Resonance main villain (ah Hung) tends to do cleanup and will ignore any hand waiving at all times. Regardless, poor service from the short red hair staff. For the two ladies that have long hair and straight black hair, they were efficient but may also be affiliated with the small business. Tea: after one round, tea flavor is gone. It took the 3rd person to finally give us new tea leaves. Payment: tea was waived, I assume its new opening so they are waiving. When asked to pay, they said if I can pay cash because tea is waived. I said no, the staff did not look happy. In a business perspective, some businesses understand that cashless payment versus cash is inevitable and understands the charges for the fees. This comes with the territory of opening a business. Either that, go cash only and understand you will be working with specific niche if thats the way you want to go. Uses Clover POS system but doesnt take Apple watch payment (tried several times but it says try again). Physical card tap works, had to take out my debit card for transaction to go through. Rice roll never came, I asked them to take it off the menu. But she said shell followup; however, I had to tell her firmly to take it off (this was right after the the 2nd item came and was foul). She respectfully said to take it off the menu and also came back with the rice rolls but I was firm and said I dont want it anymore. After I paid, I then told her about the foul food items to which they said, why didnt you tell us? Typical Chinese way will always be Ill give you a new one which is what Im not interested. I was then given a to-go box of pastries free of charge (again turned it down). I have dignity and pride giving honest food reviews and I come from moral values. And Im also not those terrible customers that take advantage of businesses either for getting free food (to that I say they are scammers).

RAW FOOD!!We ordered a fish and chips but the fish is still raw. Also the overall hygiene of the restaurant is unsatisfactory as well since you can see a lot of food debris on the floor and it s slippery and greasy.

I booked for 10am . I like the new renovations in the place and the big booth. However I found the food was just ok. It s cheaper than most places, but I ve had better in that price point. The service was bad too. Barely got any service and my friend was just finishing her last bite and we were packing our food, the server came over and said  you ve been here for 1.5 hours I m going to start cleaning . It just felt like she was trying to rush us out, keep in mind they still had empty tables and no line at the door. I was already going to leave, but that last interaction left a bitter memory. We won t be coming back.
Food is not too bad and the price is reasonable . The service is no good. By the day I was there ,a waitress let people jump the line.

Disappointed in portion and price. service was meh. Waitresses busy talking amongst themselves then serving. They missed entering our order and we waited 30 mins for our food. Had no water left and nobody bothered filling it up. Can find better pricing and portion elsewhere. There was droppings on the seat as well.
Food was alright but the service.... if I could go negative stars I would. They asked us to please pay and finish up after eating only an hour saying we sat there already for to long.
Food was ok,  But The Waitress who collecting moneye attitude was extremely poor, wearing a scowl throughout, not even a thank you when taking the money. Definitely wont be returning!
The food was not good at all, nothing was fresh. Come at your own risk.
The food is garbage and so are the people!  Too bad you can t give zero or negative stars!
The service was painfully slow.
The food is terrible, will not come again
Never gonna visit again.  Money wasted.

The meal was served too slowly, from 7pm to 8:30, there was no soup, and I was hungry... I ordered half a chicken, and finally asked about no sunbathing compared to the belated arrival at the isolation table...

Its simply garbage among garbage. The food is very slow. The ribs have a bad smell. The beef tripe only has beef tendon. The service attitude is extremely bad. I suggest you dont waste your money! ! !

Im really speechless. They are all fake reviews. The shrimp dumpling skin is so thick, the fresh bamboo rolls look like they have been frozen for a long time, the chicken feet are fried to pieces, and the beef tendon tastes rancid. They are all frozen snacks. I want to eat quick frozen ones. , I will not go to the supermarket to buy it myself, never come again. You can t refill the 2.99 West Toast for afternoon tea. You have to order another afternoon tea meal before you can refill it. Did you write it on the menu? Boss, are you so busy with customers?
